<div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
  <div class="lg:col-span-2">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">Research Paper Word Count Estimator</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8 leading-relaxed">Estimate how many words your paper will be based on page count, font, spacing, margins, and font size.</p>

    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "leaderboard" %></div>

    <div data-controller="research-paper-word-count-calculator ad-engagement" class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:gap-8">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <label for="rpwc-pages" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Number of Pages</label>
            <input id="rpwc-pages" type="number" inputmode="decimal" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="pageCount" data-action="input->research-paper-word-count-calculator#calculate" class="w-full" placeholder="10" step="1" min="1">
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="rpwc-font" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Font</label>
            <select id="rpwc-font" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="font" data-action="change->research-paper-word-count-calculator#calculate" class="w-full">
              <option value="times_new_roman" selected>Times New Roman</option>
              <option value="arial">Arial</option>
              <option value="calibri">Calibri</option>
              <option value="courier">Courier</option>
              <option value="georgia">Georgia</option>
              <option value="verdana">Verdana</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="rpwc-spacing" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Line Spacing</label>
            <select id="rpwc-spacing" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="spacing" data-action="change->research-paper-word-count-calculator#calculate" class="w-full">
              <option value="double" selected>Double</option>
              <option value="1.5">1.5 Spacing</option>
              <option value="single">Single</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="rpwc-margins" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Margins</label>
            <select id="rpwc-margins" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="margins" data-action="change->research-paper-word-count-calculator#calculate" class="w-full">
              <option value="1_inch" selected>1 inch (standard)</option>
              <option value="1.25_inch">1.25 inch</option>
              <option value="1.5_inch">1.5 inch</option>
              <option value="0.75_inch">0.75 inch</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="rpwc-size" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Font Size</label>
            <select id="rpwc-size" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="fontSize" data-action="change->research-paper-word-count-calculator#calculate" class="w-full">
              <option value="10">10 pt</option>
              <option value="11">11 pt</option>
              <option value="12" selected>12 pt</option>
              <option value="13">13 pt</option>
              <option value="14">14 pt</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <input id="rpwc-refs" type="checkbox" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="hasReferences" data-action="change->research-paper-word-count-calculator#calculate" class="rounded border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500">
            <label for="rpwc-refs" class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Exclude reference pages</label>
          </div>
          <div class="hidden" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="referencePagesField">
            <label for="rpwc-ref-pages" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Reference Pages</label>
            <input id="rpwc-ref-pages" type="number" inputmode="decimal" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="referencePages" data-action="input->research-paper-word-count-calculator#calculate" class="w-full" placeholder="1" step="0.5" min="0" value="1">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 dark:from-green-900/20 dark:to-emerald-900/20 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-5">Word Count Estimate</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Estimated Words</span>
              <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="estimatedWords">0</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Words per Page</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="wordsPerPage">0</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Content Pages</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="contentPages">0</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Reading Time</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="readingTime">0 min</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Speaking Time</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="speakingTime">0 min</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Est. Paragraphs</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="estimatedParagraphs">0</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Est. Sentences</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" data-research-paper-word-count-calculator-target="estimatedSentences">0</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <button data-action="click->research-paper-word-count-calculator#copy" class="mt-6 w-full px-4 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-600 to-emerald-600 hover:from-green-700 hover:to-emerald-700 text-white rounded-xl shadow-sm shadow-green-500/20 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-green-500/25 transition-all duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-green-500 focus:ring-offset-2 text-sm font-medium">Copy Results</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%= render "shared/calculator_rating", slug: "research-paper-word-count" %>
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_results" %></div>

    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>How to Use the Research Paper Word Count Estimator</h2>
      <p>
        Select your paper's formatting options including font, line spacing, margins, and font size, then enter the number of pages. The estimator calculates the approximate word count based on standard typographic measurements. If your paper includes a bibliography or references section, check the exclude option and specify how many pages are references to get an accurate content word count.
      </p>
      <p>
        The standard academic format of 12-point Times New Roman with double spacing and 1-inch margins yields approximately 250 words per page. This is the baseline used by most universities and academic style guides including APA, MLA, and Chicago. Variations in font, spacing, and margins can change the word count by 15-50% in either direction.
      </p>

      <div class="my-6"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %></div>

      <h2>Common Academic Paper Lengths</h2>
      <p>
        A typical college essay ranges from 3-5 pages (750-1,250 words double-spaced). Research papers commonly require 8-12 pages (2,000-3,000 words). A senior thesis or capstone project may be 20-40 pages (5,000-10,000 words). Graduate dissertations can range from 100-300 pages (25,000-75,000 words). Understanding these benchmarks helps you plan your writing time and research scope accordingly.
      </p>

      <h3>Formatting Tricks to Avoid</h3>
      <p>
        Professors are well aware of formatting tricks used to inflate page count. Increasing margins from 1 inch to 1.25 inches, using a slightly larger font size, or widening character spacing may add a page but are easily detected. Instead, focus on developing your arguments thoroughly, providing additional evidence, or adding relevant examples to meet page requirements authentically.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>How many words are on a page with double spacing?</h3>
      <p>A standard double-spaced page with 12-point Times New Roman font and 1-inch margins contains approximately 250 words.</p>

      <h3>Does font choice affect word count per page?</h3>
      <p>Yes, different fonts have different character widths. Times New Roman fits about 250 words per double-spaced page, while Arial yields about 225 and Courier about 210.</p>

      <h3>How do margins affect word count?</h3>
      <p>Wider margins reduce the text area and word count per page. Standard 1-inch margins produce the highest word count. Increasing to 1.25-inch margins reduces words by roughly 8%.</p>

      <h3>Should I count references in my word count?</h3>
      <p>In most academic contexts, the word count refers to the body text only, excluding the title page, abstract, references, appendices, and figure captions. Always check your assignment guidelines.</p>

      <h3>How accurate is pages-to-words conversion?</h3>
      <p>Estimates based on formatting parameters are typically accurate within 5-10% for standard academic text. Factors like headings, block quotes, and lists can cause variation.</p>

      <%= render "shared/print_button" %>
      <%= render "shared/calculation_email_capture" %>
    </article>

    <%= render "shared/related_calculators", related: [
      { name: "Class Schedule Builder", description: "Build your weekly class schedule and detect time conflicts.", path: education_class_schedule_builder_path, icon_path: "M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z" },
      { name: "Credit Transfer Calculator", description: "Calculate transferable credits and estimated time savings.", path: education_credit_transfer_path, icon_path: "M8 7h12m0 0l-4-4m4 4l-4 4m0 6H4m0 0l4 4m-4-4l4-4" },
      { name: "Scholarship ROI Calculator", description: "Calculate hourly return on scholarship applications.", path: education_scholarship_roi_path, icon_path: "M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2z" }
    ] %>

    <%= render "shared/calculator_disclaimer", category: "education" %>
  </div>

  <div class="hidden lg:block">
    <div class="sticky top-24"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "sidebar" %></div>
  </div>
</div>
